scene.message:
Maki: The demons in town{nl}
suddenly increased — that was{nl}
just recently.{waitkey}{clearbox}But even though they've{nl}
increased, you don't hear{nl}
much about people getting{nl}
attacked.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Demons that don't{nl}
attack people... yet we're{nl}
being attacked, in fact.{waitkey}{clearbox}Are the demons choosing their{nl}
targets? {wait_fr:32}Surely not...{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: Quit making such a{nl}
grim face all the time and{nl}
lighten up! That's what I'm{nl}
saying!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: My skin's been a bit{nl}
rough lately...{waitkey}{clearbox}Fighting Demons is rather{nl}
Hard work, after all.{waitkey}{ret}

Brown: Lately the fatigue just{nl}
won't go away. Even I can't{nl}
beat getting older, huh.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: Until recently,{nl}
you only had to watch for{nl}
demons when the girl in black{nl}
appeared.{waitkey}{clearbox}But now demons prowl around{nl}
even without the girl there.{nl}
It's unsettling.{waitkey}{ret}

Townsperson: Everyone fears{nl}
the demons, but I don't think{nl}
there's any need to worry.{waitkey}{clearbox}I'm sure we won't be attacked.{nl}
I just have that feeling.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: Do you know my{nl}
fool of a son?{waitkey}{clearbox}A cute girl transferred into{nl}
his very class, and yet{waitkey}{clearbox}they don't get along, and he{nl}
won't even speak to her.{wait_fr:32}{nl}
Ah, medicine? Right, right.{waitkey}{ret}

Shopkeeper: Whoa, open that{nl}
and my pet frogs'll come{nl}
hopping out!{waitkey}Ha~ Gotcha!{waitkey}{ret}
